Package data

Class TensorflowLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • data.TensorflowLoader
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Controller_Tensorflow_ClassifyActionsPerTimestep, GamePredictor, PlayableGamePredictor
    public abstract class TensorflowLoader
extends java.lang.Object
    Basic utilities and loaders for getting TensorFlow models in here and working. Users should extend this class. Specifically applies to networks which take a game state and return a single list of numbers.
    Author:
    matt

    • Method Detail

      • sisoFloatPrediction

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.Float> sisoFloatPrediction​(State state,
                                                              java.lang.String inputName,
                                                              java.lang.String outputName)
        Simple prediction from the model where we give a state and expect a list of floats out. Only applies when a single output (could be multi-element though) is required from the graph.
        Parameters:
        state - State to feed into the computational graph.
        inputName - Name of the graph input to shove the state into.
        outputName - Name of the graph output to fetch.
        Returns:
        List of values returned by the specified graph output.

      • printTensorflowGraphOperations

        public void printTensorflowGraphOperations()
        Print out all operations in the TensorFlow graph to help determine which ones we want to use. There can be an incredible number, and sometimes TensorBoard is the best way to sort this out.

      • flattenState

        public static float[][] flattenState​(State state)
        Make a State object into a 72-element array the way TensorFlow wants it. This method also subtracts the torso x-component out of all body parts.
        Parameters:
        state - Input state to flatten into an array.
        Returns:
        A 1x72 element array containing all the concatenated state variable values, with the torso x-component subtracted out.
